  abstract = {We present major modifications to the Markov chain Monte Carlo inversion method of Korenaga and Karato (2008), which was developed to analyze rock deformation data and determine a corresponding flow law and its uncertainty. The uncertainties of state variables, e.g., temperature, pressure, and stress, are now taken into account by data randomization, to avoid parameter bias that could be introduced by the original implementation of the cost function. Also, it is now possible to handle a flow law composed of both parallel and sequential deformation
